  <p>The <strong>water cycle</strong> (hydrological cycle) is the continuous movement of water on, above, and below Earth's surface. It is a <strong>closed system</strong> globally — no water enters or leaves the planet. However, individual drainage basins are <strong>open systems</strong> with inputs (precipitation) and outputs (evapotranspiration, channel flow to sea).</p>
